[src:generalized-additive-models/backfitting-algorithm] The choice of when to stop the algorithm is arbitrary and it is hard to know a priori how long reaching a specific convergence threshold will take.
[src:generalized-additive-models/backfitting-algorithm] Also, the final model depends on the order in which the predictor variables $X_{i}$ are fit.
[src:generalized-additive-models/backfitting-algorithm] As well, the solution found by the backfitting procedure is non-unique.
